  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: User can sign transaction with empty password if password was entered previously but transaction was cancelled\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nUser must enter password if password field is empty. Button Sign Transaction should be not active if password field is empty. If user taps on inactive Sign Transaction then nothing should happen\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUser can sign transaction when password field is empty. For this user needs to send transaction, enter password in the popup, cancel it and Sign transaction again\r\n### Reproduction\r\nYou need to have some funds in the Wallet\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Wallet\r\n- tap on Send Transaction\r\n- as recipient select Recent recipients -> Jarrad\r\n- as amount type 0\r\n- tap Sign Transaction\r\n- type valid password in the popup\r\n- DO NOT tap on Sign transaction to continue, tap on Cancel\r\n- tap Sign Transaction again\r\n- Note that password field is empty. Tap on Sign Transaction\r\n- Observe if transaction is sent (in my case it is because Transaction sent screen is shown). It's expected that transaction will not be sent as user didn't provide password when Signing transaction second time\r\nhttps://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8112310/sessions/19/?accessToken=CMu2Ps5klJMfgvS7uhwqi6xLIzk\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly build Apr 16\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8112310/sessions/19/?accessToken=CMu2Ps5klJMfgvS7uhwqi6xLIzk\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.16 (2429) @19</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
